name: Bristles - Oceans' Meeting
description:
At the south-west tip of Western Australia stands a lighthouse on the edge of the small town of Augusta, at the intersection of the Indian and Southern Oceans. Every year tourists flock to the windy coastline to view migrating Humpback Whales and calving Southern Right Whales.

Original photography filtered through the lens of generative abstraction. Digital oil painted onto a noisy geometric canvas. 6000x6000. Made in Processing.
